<DOC><DOCNO> AP880414-0019 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-14-88 0133EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Nigeria-Corrupt     04-14 0109</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Nigeria-Corrupt,0111</SECOND><HEAD>14 Traffic Officers Arrested For Corruption</HEAD><DATELINE>LAGOS, Nigeria (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Detectives arrested 14 police officersworking at police checkpoints around Lagos for allegedly demandingbribes from motorists, a Lagos newspaper reported.   The detectives raided several checkpoints Tuesday on a 20-milespan of highway between Lagos and Ogun state, the National Concordreported. One of the officers arrested was an assistant policesuperintendent.   The equivalent of $75 in Nigerian currency was found under thefloor mat of a squad car at one checkpoint, the newspaper reportedWednesday.   Authorities began a crackdown on police corruption because ofcomplaints from the public and recent violent anti-policedemonstrations in Lagos.</TEXT></DOC>